Refactor code structure for improved readability and maintainability

Refactor backend API server for model management and initialization
- Introduced ModelManager class to handle model initialization and cleanup. - Moved model setup and LLM initialization into the ModelManager. - Updated detection and caption generation endpoints to use ModelManager. - Added error handling and status reporting for model initialization. - Implemented cleanup on server shutdown to free resources.
Enhance frontend video capture component
- Simplified video capture logic by removing unnecessary state management. - Improved error handling during frame processing and rendering. - Updated UI to better reflect video upload and processing states. - Added processing result display with detailed analysis after video processing.
Update API client to handle server-side rendering
- Modified API client to check for server-side execution and return mock data accordingly. - Updated health check and video processing functions to handle server-side scenarios.
Integrate Prisma for database management
- Added Prisma client setup for database interactions. - Created a new route for storing video analysis results in the database. - Defined Prisma schema for Detection model to store analysis data.
Update package dependencies
- Added @prisma/client to package dependencies for database management.
